textBody:
IPA is the International Phonetic Alphabet, a system of phonetic notation.

IPA may also refer to:

Organizations

* Institute of Public Affairs, Poland
* Instituto Superior Autónomo de Estudos Politécnicos, Portugal
* Independent Psychiatric Association of Russia

International

* International Phonetic Association, the organisation behind the International Phonetic Alphabet
* Insolvency Practitioners Association, of the UK and Ireland
* Institute of Public Administration (disambiguation)
* International Permafrost Association
* International Play Association
* International Police Association
* International Police Academy, operated by the US Office of Public Safety
* International Polka Association
* International Professional Pool Association, a governing body for players of pool
* International Psychoanalytical Association
* International Publishers Association

Australia

* Institute of Public Accountants
* Institute of Public Affairs

United Kingdom

* Institute of Practitioners in Advertising
* Involvement and Participation Association, an organisation devoted to the promotion of employee involvement and voice in the workplace

United States

* Independent Pilots Association
* Independence Party of America
* Institute for Propaganda Analysis
* Institute for Public Accuracy
* Island Pacific Academy, a school in Hawaii
* Innovations for Poverty Action
* Independent practice association, term for an association of physicians
* Innovative Products of America, a tool manufacturer

Science and technology

* Ipa, a genus of spiders
* Intermediate power amplifier, a part of a radio transmitter

Chemistry

* 3-Indolepropionic acid, a tryptophan metabolite that is produced by human intestinal microbiota
* Isopropyl alcohol, rubbing alcohol
* Isophthalic acid, precursor for advanced polymers and fire resistant materials
* Isopropyl acetate, solvent used in some inks and perfumes

Computing

* FreeIPA, an LDAP-based user-authentication computer-software suite for identity, policy and audit
* Intelligent personal assistant, a type of software
* Interprocedural analysis, a computer-optimization technique
* .ipa (file extension), extension for Apple iOS applications
* Ingenuity Pathway Analysis, software for biologists from Ingenuity Systems
* Information Processing Architecture, an International Computers Limited proprietary networking-software stack

Other uses

* India pale ale, a style of beer
* Important Plant Areas, a programme set up in the UK by the organisation Plantlife
* Indigenous Protected Area, Australia
* Instrument for Pre-Accession Assistance, funding assistance programme of the EU
* Interpretative phenomenological analysis, an approach to psychological qualitative research
* Investigatory Powers Act 2016, a UK surveillance law
